<%- contentFor('body') %>
<main class="faqs-container">
  <div class="faqs-header">
    <h1 class="faqs-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="faqs-subtitle">Everything you need to know about Puff of Air</p>
  </div>

  <section class="faqs-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        How do I search for weather?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Enter any city name in the search box on the home page and click
          Search. You'll get real-time weather conditions including temperature,
          humidity, wind speed, and more.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        Where does the weather data come from?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          We use the
          <a
            href="https://openweathermap.org"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >OpenWeatherMap API</a
          >
          — one of the most trusted weather data providers in the world, with
          data from over 40,000 weather stations globally.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        How accurate is the weather data?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Current weather data is updated every 10 minutes from local weather
          stations. Accuracy varies by location — major cities tend to have more
          precise readings than rural areas.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        What does "Feels Like" temperature mean?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Feels Like accounts for humidity and wind speed to give you a more
          realistic sense of how the temperature will feel on your skin — not
          just what the thermometer reads.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        Why are temperatures shown in Fahrenheit?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          The current version displays temperatures in Fahrenheit. A unit toggle
          for Celsius is planned for a future update.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">
        Can I search by country code?
        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Yes — for more precise results you can enter a city and country code
          together, for example "London, GB" or "Paris, FR". This helps when
          multiple cities share the same name.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
